text: The rainbow cale (Heteroscarus acroptilus) is a species of weed whiting endemic to Australia where it is found in marine waters along the southern coast. == References == # Froese, Rainer; Pauly, Daniel (eds.) (2019). "Heteroscarus acroptilus" in FishBase. August 2019 version. Category:Labriformes
title: Rainbow cale
